&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 7 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clinical Pharmacist – Assessment Unit - Surgical, Medical &amp; Ambulatory 1.0WTE with emergency duty commitment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Princess Alexandra Hospital NHS Trust &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are very pleased to be able to offer new and exciting posts working in our brand new Assessment Units.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The new Medical and Surgical Assessment Centre will be a two-storey extension adjacent to the emergency department (ED) at the front of the hospital and next to Charnley Ward. This will improve the facilities available for our patients ahead of the completion of the new hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for well-rounded pharmacists with excellent team-working and communication skills to provide a high quality clinical pharmacy service to the new Assessment Units, including ambulatory and surgical units.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of a dedicated pharmacy team, you will work a variety of 8hr and 12hr shifts to provide a 7 day service, as part of the multidisciplinary team in a patient-facing role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are looking for the opportunity to work in a newly created role, would like a job that condenses work hours into fewer days or simply a new challenge please do apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact John Biddulph, Chief Pharmacist, Princess Alexandra Hospital on 01279 827349, Vicky Thompson, Lead pharmacist Education and training on 01279 444455 Ext 2848 or Ceri Fisher, Lead pharmacist Education and training on 01279 827349&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMr John BiddulphJob titleChief PharmacistEmail addressjohn.biddulph@nhs.netTelephone number01279827349&lt;/p&gt;
